news.title: Noida authority to issue notices to 250 farmhouses on Yamuna floodplains
news.para: Officials said while buying and selling land in this area is not illegal, using the land for anything other than agriculture — like building farmhouses or permanent constructions — is prohibited.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government mulls hike in property registration rebate for women to ₹1 crore
news.para: "This would empower women and enhance their participation in the economy," the CM said during a review of the department of stamp and registration on Friday.

news.title: Belagavi cantonment board sends revised building bylaws for approval
news.para: ​The updated draft incorporates several changes to building permissions, aligning with recommendations from The Energy and Resources Institute (TERI), after the previous version was struck down by authorities.

news.title: Birla Corporation's net profit rises 32.7% in Q4 FY25
news.para: ​Birla Corporation informed the bourses after a board meeting held on Friday that consolidated total income increased 6.8 per cent at Rs 2,863.14 crore as against Rs 2,680.13 crore in the previous similar period.

news.title: Delhi HC restrains WTC Noida from using trademarks of World Trade Centres Association
news.para: ​Justice Amit Bansal said a prima facie case was in favour of WTCA and against WTC Noida and its promoters including Ashish Bhalla, related to Bhalla Group of Companies.

news.title: LondonMetric buys Urban Logistics for $925 million
news.para: LondonMetric made its first proposal for Urban Logistics in April and raised the bid a week later. The final offer represents a 22.2% premium to Urban Logistics's closing share price on April 10, a day before the proposal was publicly confirmed.

news.title: Puravankara Group to jointly develop 24.59-acre land in Bengaluru
news.para: Abhishek Kapoor has resigned from the position of CEO and executive director of Puravankara Group.

news.title: CoStar to buy Australia's Domain in $1.9 billion deal
news.para: After weeks of due diligence by CoStar, which owns a 16.9% stake in Domain, the companies have agreed on the U.S. firm's A$4.43 apiece offer.

news.title: ICICI Venture to shift PE, real estate funds businesses to ICICI Prudential AMC
news.para: The move is aimed at consolidating investment offerings under ICICI Prudential AMC, so it can provide a full suite of asset classes, including private equity, the bank said in an exchange filing.

news.title: Indore civic body to build 1,000 PMAY flats in Sidhora
news.para: Under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) 2.0, in-principle approval was granted for the Detailed Project Report (DPR) for the construction of over 1,000 houses in Gram Sindhora.

news.title: Nagpur civic body clears encroachments on Khamla plot for five-star hotel construction
news.para: NMC officials from Laxmi Nagar zone, supported by police personnel, executed the drive by evicting vendors near the mutton market and installing iron railings along the footpath to prevent re-encroachment.

news.title: Amrita Puri and family buy apartment in Mumbai for ₹37 crore
news.para: The apartment is situated in World One, a part of The World Towers developed by the Lodha Group, and has a built-up area of 505.85 sq meters (5,446.53 sq ft).

news.title: Ludhiana: LIT urges property owners to avail of one-time settlement schemes
news.para: LIT Chairman Tarsem Bhinder said that the local bodies department issued two one-time relaxation policies for the allottees, those transferred, and owners of properties falling under development schemes of LIT.

news.title: Property owners question Bengaluru development body over additional cess
news.para: What has added to taxpayers' frustration is not the increase, but the complete lack of clarity about it: Not even some officials within the civic authority know why the cess is being collected!

news.title: Amazon India entities lease over one lakh sq ft office space in Mumbai’s Vikhroli
news.para: The lock-in period is set at 48 months for the licensees, and for the entire lease duration in the case of the licensor. The agreements were registered on April 30, showed the documents accessed through CRE Matrix.

news.title: Mhada urges redevelopment of cessed buildings in Mumbai island city
news.para: . This allows landowners the first opportunity to submit a redevelopment proposal to the Mhada board within six months with the irrevocable consent of 51% of tenants/residents.

news.title: Odisha RERA seeks government action on promoter violation
news.para: The request was made by the authority upon revelation that many promoters have been overlooking this important provision of RERA and fraudulently obtaining approval for revised building plans from the planning authorities.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government's town planning revamp slows down approvals
news.para: As per the new rules, the LTPs have been empowered to design, upload to the portal and monitor the construction of private buildings.

news.title: About 60 companies, builders in Gurugram extracting groundwater illegally: HWRA panel
news.para: Most of these sites, where groundwater is being extracted, are in New Gurgaon – an area that was until a few years ago covered by farmlands, but it is now densely populated with dozens of housing societies lined along the Dwarka Expressway.

news.title: For now, Greater Bengaluru unlikely to go beyond BBMP limits
news.para: The state cabinet, which will meet Friday, is expected to discuss the matter with a decision on the date of implementation of Greater Bengaluru Governance Act-2024, which was notified on April 24.
